title: Did Jack Branning swear on EastEnders as he ranted about Roxyâ€™s drug-taking?
text:
Comments EASTENDERS fans were left questioning whether Jack Branning swore pre-watershed on EastEnders tonight. 
Jack (Scott Maslen) was ranting about Roxyâ€™s drug taking when he appeared to blurt out the swear word. Jack Branning appears to swear on EastEnders as he rants after inquest 
He had attended the inquest into his wife Ronnie and sister Roxy's death with his brother Max (Jake Wood). 
The grief-stricken man let it all out after the coroner ruled that "misadventure" led to their deaths. 
Jack ranted: "Is that what I'm going to tell Amy? An adventure gone wrong? Well it's not true, is it. Roxy went into that water knowing full well she put a [shed? s***?] load of gear up her nose." Did Jack Branning swear on tonight's episode of EastEnders? 

Fans were shocked, thinking that Jack had said the latter, with some even threatening to call Ofcom. 
One remarked: "Did Jack just say "a s*** load"? ha. #eastenders." 
Another ranted: "Jack just said 's***load' on #Eastenders I'm shook and already on the phone to OFCOM. RELATED STORIES 'GET OUT!' A viewer commented: "did jack branning really just say 'Roxy put a s*** load of that gear up her nose' ðŸ˜³ðŸ˜‚#eastenders." 
But one took a screen grab showing subtitles claiming it said "shed load". 
They commented: "Genuinely thought jack said 's*** load' but alas I was wrong #eastenders." 
An EastEnders rep confirmed to The Sun Online that Jack did indeed say "shed". EastEnders airs Monday, Tuesday, Thursday and Friday nights on BBC One
